Document: RichTextLabel
Path: godot/classes/class_richtextlabel.rst
Summary: An overview of the RichTextLabel control for displaying formatted text, including important notes on how it handles text updates, BBCode, paragraphs, and alignment.

RichTextLabel is a control for displaying text that can contain custom fonts, images, and basic formatting. It manages these as an internal tag stack and adapts itself to the given width and height.

Note: The methods `newline`, `push_paragraph`, the characters `\n` and `\r\n`, the `p` tag, and alignment tags all start a new paragraph. Each paragraph is processed independently in its own BiDi context. To force line wrapping within a paragraph, other line breaking characters can be used, such as Form Feed (U+000C), Next Line (U+0085), or Line Separator (U+2028).

Note: Assignments to the `text` property clear the tag stack and reconstruct it from the property's contents. Any edits made to `text` will erase previous edits made from other manual sources such as `append_text` and the `push_*` / `pop` methods.

Note: RichTextLabel does not support entangled BBCode tags. For example, instead of using `[b]bold[i]bold italic[/b]italic[/i]`, use `[b]bold[i]bold italic[/i][/b][i]italic[/i]`.

Note: The `push_*` and `pop` functions do not affect BBCode.

Note: While `bbcode_enabled` is enabled, alignment tags such as `[center]` will take priority over the `horizontal_alignment` setting which determines the default text alignment.
---CHUNK---
