Path: godot/classes/class_richtextlabel.rst
Summary: A list of RichTextLabel's properties, including their data types and default values, covering text layout, BBCode processing, selection, scrolling, and visibility.

* autowrap_mode (AutowrapMode): The autowrap mode for the text. See AutowrapMode for options. Default: `3`.
* autowrap_trim_flags (bitfield[LineBreakFlag]): The line breaking and trimming behavior for autowrapping. See LineBreakFlag. Default: `192`.
* bbcode_enabled (bool): If `true`, the label uses BBCode formatting. Default: `false`.
* clip_contents (bool): If `true`, the control clips the content when it exceeds its boundaries. Default: `true` (overrides Control).
* context_menu_enabled (bool): If `true`, a right-click context menu will be available. Default: `false`.
* custom_effects (Array): The custom effects used for formatting. The array should contain RichTextEffect resources. Default: `[]`.
* deselect_on_focus_loss_enabled (bool): If `true`, the selection is lost when the control loses focus. Default: `true`.
* drag_and_drop_selection_enabled (bool): If `true`, selected text can be dragged and dropped. Default: `true`.
* fit_content (bool): If `true`, the label's minimum size will expand to fit its content. Note: This property is used for editor visuals and is not available in exported projects. Default: `false`.
* focus_mode (FocusMode): The focus access mode. See FocusMode for options. Default: `3` (overrides Control).
* hint_underlined (bool): If `true`, the hint text is underlined. Default: `true`.
* horizontal_alignment (HorizontalAlignment): The horizontal alignment of the text. Default: `0`.
* justification_flags (bitfield[JustificationFlag]): The justification flags for the text. See JustificationFlag for options. Default: `163`.
* language (String): The language code used for text shaping algorithms. Default: `""`.
* meta_underlined (bool): If `true`, text in `[meta]` tags is underlined. Default: `true`.
* progress_bar_delay (int): The delay in milliseconds for the `[progress]` tag. Default: `1000`.
* scroll_active (bool): If `true`, the scrollbar is visible. Setting this to `false` is equivalent to `set_v_scroll_enabled(false)` and `set_h_scroll_enabled(false)`. Default: `true`.
* scroll_following (bool): If `true`, the viewport scrolls to the bottom when new text is added. Default: `false`.
* scroll_following_visible_characters (bool): If `true`, the viewport scrolls to make the last visible character visible when `visible_characters` or `visible_ratio` is changed. Default: `false`.
* selection_enabled (bool): If `true`, text can be selected. Default: `false`.
* shortcut_keys_enabled (bool): If `true`, shortcut keys for context menu items are enabled. Default: `true`.
* structured_text_bidi_override (StructuredTextParser): Sets the parser for structured text. Default: `0`.
* structured_text_bidi_override_options (Array): Options used for structured text. Default: `[]`.
* tab_size (int): The number of spaces a tab character represents. Default: `4`.
* tab_stops (PackedFloat32Array): An array of custom tab stop positions in pixels. Default: `PackedFloat32Array()`.
* text (String): The entire text content of the label, including any BBCode. Default: `""`.
* text_direction (TextDirection): The base text writing direction. Default: `0`.
* threaded (bool): If `true`, the label will perform layout and resizing calculations on a separate thread. Default: `false`.
* vertical_alignment (VerticalAlignment): The vertical alignment of the text. Default: `0`.
* visible_characters (int): The number of characters to display. A value of `-1` displays all characters. This can be used to create a "typewriter" effect. Default: `-1`.
* visible_characters_behavior (VisibleCharactersBehavior): The behavior for displaying `visible_characters`. See VisibleCharactersBehavior for options. Default: `0`.
* visible_ratio (float): The fraction of characters to display, from 0.0 to 1.0. Default: `1.0`.
---CHUNK---
