Document: RichTextLabel
Path: godot/classes/class_richtextlabel.rst
Summary: This chunk details the theme properties for RichTextLabel, including default colors for text, selection, and tables; constants for line spacing, shadows, and outlines; font and font size overrides for bold, italics, and mono styles; and styleboxes for focus and normal states.

Theme Property Descriptions

* default_color (Color): The default text color. Default: `Color(1, 1, 1, 1)`.
* font_outline_color (Color): The default tint of text outline. Default: `Color(0, 0, 0, 1)`.
* font_selected_color (Color): The color of selected text, used when `selection_enabled` is `true`. If equal to `Color(0, 0, 0, 0)`, it will be ignored. Default: `Color(0, 0, 0, 0)`.
* font_shadow_color (Color): The color of the font's shadow. Default: `Color(0, 0, 0, 0)`.
* selection_color (Color): The color of the selection box. Default: `Color(0.1, 0.1, 1, 0.8)`.
* table_border (Color): The default cell border color. Default: `Color(0, 0, 0, 0)`.
* table_even_row_bg (Color): The default background color for even rows. Default: `Color(0, 0, 0, 0)`.
* table_odd_row_bg (Color): The default background color for odd rows. Default: `Color(0, 0, 0, 0)`.
* line_separation (int): Additional vertical spacing between lines (in pixels), spacing is added to line descent. This value can be negative. Default: `0`.
* outline_size (int): The size of the text outline. Default: `0`. Note: If using a font with `FontFile.multichannel_signed_distance_field` enabled, its `FontFile.msdf_pixel_range` must be set to at least *twice* the value of `outline_size` for outline rendering to look correct. Otherwise, the outline may appear to be cut off earlier than intended.
* paragraph_separation (int): Additional vertical spacing between paragraphs (in pixels). Spacing is added after the last line. This value can be negative. Default: `0`.
* shadow_offset_x (int): The horizontal offset of the font's shadow. Default: `1`.
* shadow_offset_y (int): The vertical offset of the font's shadow. Default: `1`.
* shadow_outline_size (int): The size of the shadow outline. Default: `1`.
* strikethrough_alpha (int): The default strikethrough color transparency (percent). For strikethroughs with a custom color, this theme item is only used if the custom color's alpha is `0.0` (fully transparent). Default: `50`.
* table_h_separation (int): The horizontal separation of elements in a table. Default: `3`.
* table_v_separation (int): The vertical separation of elements in a table. Default: `3`.
* text_highlight_h_padding (int): The horizontal padding around boxes drawn by the `[fgcolor]` and `[bgcolor]` tags. This does not affect the appearance of text selection. To avoid any risk of neighboring highlights overlapping each other, set this to `0` to disable padding. Default: `3`.
* text_highlight_v_padding (int): The vertical padding around boxes drawn by the `[fgcolor]` and `[bgcolor]` tags. This does not affect the appearance of text selection. To avoid any risk of neighboring highlights overlapping each other, set this to `0` to disable padding. Default: `3`.
* underline_alpha (int): The default underline color transparency (percent). For underlines with a custom color, this theme item is only used if the custom color's alpha is `0.0` (fully transparent). Default: `50`.
* bold_font (Font): The font used for bold text.
* bold_italics_font (Font): The font used for bold italics text.
* italics_font (Font): The font used for italics text.
* mono_font (Font): The font used for monospace text.
* normal_font (Font): The default text font.
* bold_font_size (int): The font size used for bold text.
* bold_italics_font_size (int): The font size used for bold italics text.
* italics_font_size (int): The font size used for italics text.
* mono_font_size (int): The font size used for monospace text.
* normal_font_size (int): The default text font size.
* horizontal_rule (Texture2D): The horizontal rule texture.
* focus (StyleBox): The background used when the RichTextLabel is focused. The `focus` StyleBox is displayed *over* the base StyleBox, so a partially transparent StyleBox should be used to ensure the base StyleBox remains visible. A StyleBox that represents an outline or an underline works well for this purpose. To disable the focus visual effect, assign a StyleBoxEmpty resource. Note that disabling the focus visual effect will harm keyboard/controller navigation usability, so this is not recommended for accessibility reasons.
* normal (StyleBox): The normal background for the RichTextLabel.